-- CBS reports first revenue growth in five quarters
-- 
-- Wed May 5, 2010 4:56pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/05/05/us-cbs-idUSTRE6445HY20100505

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - CBS Corp ( CBS.N ), owner of the most-watched television network, reported its first quarterly revenue growth in more than a year, helped by a rebound in advertising. 

 Revenue increased 12 percent to $3.53 billion -- the first time CBS recorded revenue growth in five quarters -- on the comeback of advertising revenue, up 17.4 percent to $2.38 billion. Analysts had estimated revenue of $3.44 billion, according to Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S At the company's Entertainment Group, which includes shows like "How I Met Your Mother" and this year the Super Bowl, revenue advanced 15 percent to $2 billion. Revenue at its Cable Networks increased 8 percent to $368 million. CBS said revenue at its local Broadcasting Group grew 19 percent from the same period a year-ago. CBS shares hit a 52-week high on May 3 at $16.98 and are up 15 percent year-to-date. (Reporting by  Jennifer Saba ; Editing by Steve Orlofsky)